CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 12, 1941, pg. 8, reads: "Cutting Her Eighteenth Birthday Cake - Last Tuesday Henrietta Howard celebrated her eighteenth birthday at the Calanthian Home. She was feted at a birthday party by her friends.  Left to right: June Thomas, Julia Miller, Eunice Taylor, Goldie Curry, Emma Coy, Margaret Lee, Eileen McPherson [McPhierson], center, and Henrietta Howard, the guest of honor."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, left to right: June Thomas, Julia Miller, Eunice Taylor, Henrietta Howard posed behind her eighteenth birthday cake, Goldie Curry, Emma Coy, Margaret Lee, and Eileen McPhierson, in Calanthian Home
